Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.58,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so today we will finish the Greeks by discussing Aristotle.\N{\rChinese}好的，今天我们来完成对希腊的讨论，先说一说亚里士多。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.72,0:00:11.92,English,,0,0,0,,And a lot of what I will say today will be controversial.\N{\rChinese}接下来我会说的那几句，能说得很久。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.64,0:00:17.00,English,,0,0,0,,So feel free to challenge me.\N{\rChinese}其后再来回顾?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.06,0:00:19.18,English,,0,0,0,,Feel free to ask for clarification.\N{\rChinese}好，先说一说亚里士多
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.98,0:00:23.76,English,,0,0,0,,Feel free to ask any questions.\N{\rChinese}好吧！先给我点儿…???????????????????????????????????????????????????????
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.20,0:00:26.52,English,,0,0,0,,So here's my argument.\N{\rChinese}...????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.24,0:00:29.24,English,,0,0,0,,Aristotle is a paradox.\N{\rChinese}亚里士多是个悖论。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.00,0:00:33.40,English,,0,0,0,,He is one of the mysterious figures in world history.\N{\rChinese}他是世界历史中的一位神秘人物。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.52,0:00:35.96,English,,0,0,0,,He's one of the most famous, but he's one of the most mysterious.\N{\rChinese}他是个很久的…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.48,0:00:38.42,English,,0,0,0,,He's a paradox for three reasons, okay?\N{\rChinese}他是三种原因的悖论，先说…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.56,0:00:42.94,English,,0,0,0,,The first reason is he is considered\N{\rChinese}...????…??…???
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.94,0:00:47.96,English,,0,0,0,,to be one of the greatest philosophers in human history.\N{\rChinese}...??…???
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.14,0:00:53.44,English,,0,0,0,,He's next to Plato. He's certainly as influential as Plato.\N{\rChinese}他紧随柏拉托，确实与柏拉托同样有影响力。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.94,0:00:58.88,English,,0,0,0,,But what is unique about him is we do not have anything,\N{\rChinese}但他那点儿………??…??…??
