Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.26,0:02:10.04,English,,0,0,0,,He's written a book on ethics.\N{\rChinese}他写了一本关于伦理学的书
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.24,0:02:12.82,English,,0,0,0,,What is a good life? What makes a good person?\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.22,0:02:15.06,English,,0,0,0,,He's written a book on rhetoric.\N{\rChinese}We have to..??..??..??..??..??..??..??..??..??..??..??..??..??..??..
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.30,0:02:19.28,English,,0,0,0,,How do you convince the audience that you are correct?\N{\rChinese}你怎么让观众相信你是对的？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.92,0:02:24.64,English,,0,0,0,,He's also written books on physics.\N{\rChinese}他也写过关于物理的书。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.34,0:02:28.28,English,,0,0,0,,He's written books on metaphysics.\N{\rChinese}他写了关于形而学的书
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.46,0:02:29.72,English,,0,0,0,,He's written books on physics.\N{\rChinese}他写了关于物理的书
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.72,0:02:31.10,English,,0,0,0,,He's written books on biology.\N{\rChinese}他写了关于生物学的书。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.50,0:02:33.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The range is just incredible.\N{\rChinese}好的？范围真是太棒了。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.52,0:02:38.90,English,,0,0,0,,We have no analog in human history like him.\N{\rChinese}我们在历史上没有类似他的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.50,0:02:45.02,English,,0,0,0,,He's simply unique in the range of his curiosity.\N{\rChinese}他在好奇心范围里很简单的没得有。”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.08,0:02:50.02,English,,0,0,0,,Second paradox. The third paradox is most problematic.\N{\rChinese}第二个悖论。第三个悖论最为棘手。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.88,0:02:56.18,English,,0,0,0,,We know that Aristotle studied under Plato for 20 years.\N{\rChinese}我们知道阿里士多·帕特里奥斯在十里程里里程里里程里里程里里程里里程里里程里里程里里
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.02,0:02:59.70,English,,0,0,0,,And so we also believe that Aristotle studied under Plato for 20 years.\N{\rChinese}和我们一起，...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.70,0:03:05.26,English,,0,0,0,,Aristotle was Plato's most famous student.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.82,0:03:11.24,English,,0,0,0,,The paradox is Aristotle's understanding\N{\rChinese}第51句：阿里士多的理解
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.24,0:03:14.36,English,,0,0,0,,of the universe is radically\N{\rChinese}第52句：是...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.36,0:03:19.02,English,,0,0,0,,opposed to Plato's understanding of the universe.\N{\rChinese}第53句：...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.64,0:03:22.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And that's, again, is unique in human history.\N{\rChinese}好的？再一次，...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.04,0:03:28.82,English,,0,0,0,,You would think the best student would carry on the master's work or at least build on it,\N{\rChinese}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.86,0:03:30.32,English,,0,0,0,,right? But Aristotle,\N{\rChinese}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.86,0:03:31.92,English,,0,0,0,,his understanding of the universe,\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.28,0:03:37.22,English,,0,0,0,,is in conflict with Plato's work.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.44,0:03:40.02,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, you could also argue that\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.02,0:03:44.32,English,,0,0,0,,Aristotle is negating Plato's worldview.\N{\rChinese}Aristotle ... ...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.70,0:03:47.04,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So let me explain how.\N{\rChinese}好的？现在，让我来解释一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.38,0:03:50.16,English,,0,0,0,,So we know Plato. We know that for Plato,\N{\rChinese}好的，先说一下吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.40,0:03:53.58,English,,0,0,0,,there is a god, and it's called the form of the good.\N{\rChinese}有一位神，叫作“善的形式”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.40,0:03:59.68,English,,0,0,0,,And the form of the good is what is the best.\N{\rChinese}“善的形式”是最好的。”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.68,0:04:02.42,English,,0,0,0,,It's eternal, perfect,\N{\rChinese}它是永恒的，完美的，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.72,0:04:04.64,English,,0,0,0,,and immutable.\N{\rChinese}且是不变的。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.08,0:04:06.62,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Now,\N{\rChinese}好的，先说吧！
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.72,0:04:11.52,English,,0,0,0,,the form of the good emanates other perfections.\N{\rChinese}好的，先说一…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.56,0:04:14.96,English,,0,0,0,,What he calls the form of the ideal.\N{\rChinese}他所称的理想形式。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.04,0:04:19.46,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So these are concepts like justice and beauty and reason.\N{\rChinese}好的，先说吧！
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.04,0:04:23.02,English,,0,0,0,,And then these concepts manifest themselves\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.02,0:04:28.16,English,,0,0,0,,in forms like horse,\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.24,0:04:29.50,English,,0,0,0,,right? Or a woman.\N{\rChinese}对吗？或者是个女人。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.68,0:04:32.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And these are like the ideal, perfect,\N{\rChinese}好的，先说吧！
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.66,0:04:36.42,English,,0,0,0,,immutable, eternal manifestations.\N{\rChinese}不变的，永恒的表现。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.94,0:04:40.42,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So there's only one horse. It's up in heaven.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以只有一匹马。它在天上。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.56,0:04:45.60,English,,0,0,0,,Everything else is a copy of this horse or imitation of this horse.\N{\rChinese}一切其它都是这匹马的复制品或模仿。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.72,0:04:47.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So we live in a shadow realm.\N{\rChinese}好的？我们住在影子世界里。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.80,0:04:51.08,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? A shadow realm where everything is imitation.\N{\rChinese}好的？影子里一切都是模仿。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.38,0:04:53.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? This is our reality. It's a shadow reality.\N{\rChinese}好的？这是我们的一切。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.28,0:04:59.66,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why art and poetry and theater are so important.\N{\rChinese}和……好吧，...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.66,0:05:01.04,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why music and theater are so bad. Because\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.04,0:05:05.82,English,,0,0,0,,they are really an imitation of an imitation.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.28,0:05:10.74,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So this is Plato's hierarchy.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是柏拉图的层级。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.28,0:05:14.14,English,,0,0,0,,So from this hierarchy and\N{\rChinese}好的，柏拉图的层级从此开始。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.14,0:05:17.36,English,,0,0,0,,this world view, we can make certain extrapolations.\N{\rChinese}好的，柏拉古里…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.58,0:05:20.60,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The first extrapolation is for Plato,\N{\rChinese}好的？第一条推测是为柏拉图的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.80,0:05:25.20,English,,0,0,0,,what is good is if you approach or\N{\rChinese}好的，先前…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.20,0:05:26.84,English,,0,0,0,,return to the form of the good.\N{\rChinese}好的…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.00,0:05:28.24,English,,0,0,0,,What is evil?\N{\rChinese}什么是好？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.24,0:05:33.22,English,,0,0,0,,What is bad is if you move away from the form of the good.\N{\rChinese}什么是好，先前…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.36,0:05:35.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Right?\N{\rChinese}好的…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.34,0:05:39.90,English,,0,0,0,,So poetry is evil. Mathematics is good.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.08,0:05:42.62,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Now, why is mathematics good?\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.82,0:05:44.52,English,,0,0,0,,Because mathematics is what allows\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.52,0:05:49.18,English,,0,0,0,,you to approach the\N{\rChinese}你去接近
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.18,0:05:50.52,English,,0,0,0,,form of the good.\N{\rChinese}形状的好事物。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.90,0:05:53.68,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So let me give you an example of this.\N{\rChinese}全部好！让我来给你举个例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.86,0:05:56.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Let's say there's a circle.\N{\rChinese}好的？让我们说有一个圆圈。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.62,0:06:01.48,English,,0,0,0,,Right? What Plato argues is no matter how hard you try,\N{\rChinese}好的，回到本地！
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.78,0:06:03.24,English,,0,0,0,,you could never,\N{\rChinese}好的，回到……
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.30,0:06:08.08,English,,0,0,0,,ever draw a circle in this world.\N{\rChinese}在这世界里画过圆圈吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.56,0:06:11.12,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Because a circle has an edge.\N{\rChinese}好的，圆圈有边。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.48,0:06:15.18,English,,0,0,0,,So it's like literally impossible for you to create something without an edge.\N{\rChinese}于是就像是个圆圈有边的样子。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.32,0:06:17.06,English,,0,0,0,,Right? You're like, well, I can draw on the computer.\N{\rChinese}好的，...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.54,0:06:20.48,English,,0,0,0,,But if you go at a microscopic level, you will always find an edge.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.22,0:06:22.80,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So how do you create a circle?\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.12,0:06:26.08,English,,0,0,0,,Well, you create a circle by imagining it in your head.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.94,0:06:28.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So you draw a circle.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.22,0:06:32.76,English,,0,0,0,,So what you're really doing is you're imagining the circle\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.76,0:06:36.70,English,,0,0,0,,because you're accessing the realm of the forms.\N{\rChinese}因为你正在进入形式的领域。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.74,0:06:38.16,English,,0,0,0,,You're approaching from the good.\N{\rChinese}你正从善的角度来接近。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.74,0:06:40.90,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So it's only pure,\N{\rChinese}好的，...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.08,0:06:43.54,English,,0,0,0,,it is only through a process of pure thought,\N{\rChinese}它只通过纯思维的过程，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.72,0:06:46.50,English,,0,0,0,,pure philosophy, pure mathematics that\N{\rChinese}纯粘哲学，纯粘数学，方可开始理解这世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.50,0:06:50.96,English,,0,0,0,,you can actually start to understand this world.\N{\rChinese}you can actually start to understand this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.48,0:06:58.30,English,,0,0,0,,All right? That's Plato's understanding of the world.\N{\rChinese}全部好？那是柏拉图对世界的理解。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.46,0:07:02.34,English,,0,0,0,,Aristotle has a completely different understanding.\N{\rChinese}亚里士多德有着完全不同的理解。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.28,0:07:04.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So Aristotle starts with this.\N{\rChinese}好的，先前的那句…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.04,0:07:06.58,English,,0,0,0,,That God's a prime mover.\N{\rChinese}那是个神的首要动因。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.74,0:07:10.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So the prime mover, just imagine a big bag.\N{\rChinese}好的，先前…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.60,0:07:12.70,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Something explodes.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.96,0:07:14.38,English,,0,0,0,,Boom. It moves.\N{\rChinese}Boom. 它移动。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.58,0:07:17.72,English,,0,0,0,,And it forces other things to move as well.\N{\rChinese}它又能让其他物体也移动。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.22,0:07:22.36,English,,0,0,0,,So what Aristotle is saying is everything is really in motion.\N{\rChinese}所以，亚里士多德说的就是一切都在运动中。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.60,0:07:23.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Everything is change.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.70,0:07:29.04,English,,0,0,0,,Because it was all caused by the prime mover.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.76,0:07:34.60,English,,0,0,0,,And in Plato's, sorry, in Aristotle's world,\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.76,0:07:36.92,English,,0,0,0,,what is good is the good.\N{\rChinese}什么是好的就是好事
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.94,0:07:41.72,English,,0,0,0,,But what he's saying is if the thing that changes moves towards its purpose.\N{\rChinese}但方才方才方才...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.94,0:07:44.56,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Or the word he uses is called telos.\N{\rChinese}??
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.24,0:07:47.48,English,,0,0,0,,Telos. Okay?\N{\rChinese}Telos。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.60,0:07:51.30,English,,0,0,0,,If you're moving towards your purpose, you are doing good in this world.\N{\rChinese}如果你朝着自己的目标前进，你在这个世界里就是好事。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.46,0:07:56.08,English,,0,0,0,,If you're moving away from your purpose, you're doing bad in this world.\N{\rChinese}如果你离开了自己的目标，才是好事。”
